don't use `tokio::main` or whatever that spawns its own runtime. If you really only change `fn run` to `async fn run` then it should work due to https://github.com/tauri-apps/tauri/pull/11162

> Reproduction
Make run async in lib.rs

Try this in a fresh create-tauri-app project and it should work, at least it does for me.

If all that doesn't help, please share the code it complains about in your error (mod.rs Line 86)
@FabianLars if u don't mind can we connect on telegram or discord

i don't do messenger support (anymore). My instruction above were bad/unclear and a bit incorrect. Here's what i did to get it working

1) `pnpm create tauri-app`
2) `cd <project>/src-tauri`
3) `cargo add tokio --features full`
4) In lib.rs, Changed `pub fn run()` to `pub async fn run()`
5) In main.rs, Changed `fn main()` to
```rs
#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    projectname_lib::run().await;
}
```
6) `pnpm tauri dev` - no errors for me

body:
@FabianLars thank u , the patch worked. Let me know once its merged to new release. Just to summarize:


Regardless of `async main` or `sync main` , if the mobile entrypoint fc is `run`. The bug was that `async run` caused app to crash in `ios` platform.

Yep, we used the wrong `block_on` function in a mobile specific proxy thing which causes tokio's "cannot spawn runtime inside a runtime" error if the function annotated with `#[cfg_attr(mobile, tauri::mobile_entry_point)]` (by default called `fn run()`) was an async function.
